    "RandomQuantumCircuitSimulate[{p, t}, {s1, s2, ...}] simulates a random \
quantum circuit of depth 3 t on qubits {s1, s2, ...} with alternating unitary \
and measurement layers. Each unitary layer consists of randomly selected \
two-qubit unitary gates arranged in a brick-wall pattern, and in a \
measurement layer, each qubit is measured with probability p in the \
computational basis.", "synonyms" -> {}, "tabletags" -> {}, "title" -> 
